<doc id="37894" wikidata="Q3877672" url="?curid=37894" title="Savoy knot">
<text>The Savoy knot, a type of decorative knot, is a heraldic knot used primarily in Italian heraldry. It is most notable for its appearance on the heraldic badge of the House of Savoy, where it is accompanied by the motto &quot;Stringe ma non costringe&quot;, &quot;It tightens, but does not constrain&quot;. The Cavendish knot is an identical heraldic knot. In shape, the Savoy knot is comparable to a figure eight.

When used outside heraldry (as a real knot), it is known as a figure-eight knot.

The Savoy knot can also be seen on the Alfa Romeo automobile badge (founded and manufactured in Milan, Italy) up to 1943.

==See also==
*List of knots
*Order of the Most Holy Annunciation

